1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:00,833
hello everyone

2
00:00:00,833 --> 00:00:03,233
today we are going to start a new adventure in gregtech 6

3
00:00:03,233 --> 00:00:04,466
as we look around

4
00:00:04,466 --> 00:00:06,033
we notice some surface rocks

5
00:00:06,033 --> 00:00:08,600
which we can collect and use to craft our first axe

6
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:11,133
which can be crafted without even a crafting table

7
00:00:11,233 --> 00:00:12,266
this axe is cheap

8
00:00:12,266 --> 00:00:14,700
and capable of chopping down multiple logs at once

9
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:16,833
but it's slow and it has a low durability

10
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:19,600
but that's also because we made this axe out of marble pebbles

11
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,666
and if we look around a little bit more

12
00:00:21,666 --> 00:00:23,666
we can indeed find some better rocks

13
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:25,800
after spending enough time collecting rocks

14
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:28,400
we figure out that red granite is the best one

15
00:00:28,866 --> 00:00:31,800
tools made out of this rock can even harvest obsidian

16
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:33,266
but the speed isn't that good

17
00:00:33,266 --> 00:00:35,300
and since those tools are still made out of pebbles

18
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:37,066
the durability is quite low

19
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:38,433
but that's not much of a big deal

20
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:40,033
since we can just look around pebbles

21
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:41,600
to find more of that material

22
00:00:42,066 --> 00:00:43,466
once we locate the solid rock

23
00:00:43,466 --> 00:00:45,700
we just have to break the stone twice with a hammer

24
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:48,133
to obtain all of the pebbles we could possibly need

25
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:51,133
to get better tools we will want to process some metals

26
00:00:51,133 --> 00:00:53,233
but first we will be looking for a nice place

27
00:00:53,233 --> 00:00:55,300
where we can start building our industry

28
00:00:55,666 --> 00:00:57,533
since we might need chlorine in the future

29
00:00:57,533 --> 00:00:59,733
setting by the seaside is probably a good idea

30
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,600
and that totally wasn't an excuse

31
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:04,533
so we could have a nice sea house with view on the sunset

32
00:01:04,533 --> 00:01:06,333
and after all of that work

33
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:07,833
we can finally rest a little bit

34
00:01:07,833 --> 00:01:10,633
while eating some sweet berries we found on our way

35
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:15,000
and that's when we found out that eating too many sweets isn't healthy

36
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:19,200
the next day we decided to start working on a proper garden to fix our diet

37
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:20,666
but after removing some rocks

38
00:01:20,666 --> 00:01:23,933
we figured out there was a high concentration of copper in our soil

39
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,233
we started digging deeper to investigate

40
00:01:26,233 --> 00:01:29,066
and we eventually found more and more copper-rich rocks

41
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:32,533
but copper on its own is an awful material for tools

42
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:33,466
to make it stronger

43
00:01:33,466 --> 00:01:36,666
we have to add some of the tin we also found in our backyard

44
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:39,266
but to properly alloy together those two metals

45
00:01:39,266 --> 00:01:42,466
we have to heat up the mixture at 1400K

46
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:44,833
that has to be done inside a crucible

47
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:46,900
which we can easily craft with some clay

48
00:01:47,133 --> 00:01:47,900
to heat it up

49
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:50,500
we turn on a burning box underneath the crucible

50
00:01:50,833 --> 00:01:53,100
now we just have to throw the raw ingredients in

51
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:54,800
and wait for everything to melt

52
00:01:55,066 --> 00:01:56,733
once the mixture turns the right color

53
00:01:56,733 --> 00:01:59,666
we can pour out the molten metal into a pickaxe mold

54
00:02:00,266 --> 00:02:02,066
to celebrate the advent of bronze age

55
00:02:02,066 --> 00:02:03,333
we can make a jumbo sandwich

56
00:02:03,333 --> 00:02:05,400
which we can eat in a single bite

57
00:02:05,900 --> 00:02:08,933
and that's how long it took for our crucible to turn yellow

58
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:11,433
and before we could even finish that phrase

59
00:02:11,433 --> 00:02:12,666
the crucible melted

60
00:02:13,033 --> 00:02:16,333
indeed, in gregtech 6, everything has a melting point

61
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:18,200
how quickly we reach that temperature 

62
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:20,233
depends on the thermal mass we are trying to heat up

63
00:02:20,233 --> 00:02:23,033
and how much heat energy we add to the thing

64
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:27,100
while we can guess the current temperature just by looking at the color of the crucible

65
00:02:27,100 --> 00:02:29,066
a better way is to craft a thermometer

66
00:02:29,466 --> 00:02:31,600
to craft it, we will need some mercury

67
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:33,866
so we adventured in search of new minerals

68
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,266
during our exploration

69
00:02:35,266 --> 00:02:37,000
we found huge deposits of coal

70
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,200
and huge deposits of iron-rich sand

71
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:41,900
underground we found all sorts of ores

72
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,433
some of which were rather hard to notice

73
00:02:44,733 --> 00:02:46,833
we also found a weird building

74
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:49,866
once inside it turned out to be an abandoned base

75
00:02:49,866 --> 00:02:51,833
stocked with many different chemicals

76
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:54,400
and a huge amount of all sorts of metals

77
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:57,800
we even found already worked metal parts in some nearby drawers

78
00:02:57,900 --> 00:03:00,300
and as if all of those goodies weren't enough

79
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:03,666
we even found the holy grail of the bronze age: a lighter

80
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:06,133
this one has a 100 percent success rate

81
00:03:06,133 --> 00:03:08,333
and we even have some spare propane to refill it

82
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,600
and while we found mercury in this place

83
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:13,633
we still explore more areas to secure a proper source

84
00:03:14,033 --> 00:03:15,466
we cross multiple dimensions

85
00:03:15,466 --> 00:03:17,633
until we finally found a redstone vein

86
00:03:17,633 --> 00:03:20,533
which also contains cinnabar a mercury rich metal

87
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:24,066
we process the raw material to increase the yield

88
00:03:24,066 --> 00:03:25,400
finally we heated it up

89
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,833
to extract some mercury for our thermometer

90
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:32,033
with this, we can finally measure temperature more precisely

91
00:03:32,033 --> 00:03:34,066
easing the metal alloying process

92
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:39,066
the next step was to connect our thermometer to a redstone sensor

93
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:41,700
allowing us to automate a metal alloying

94
00:03:42,066 --> 00:03:42,700
to do so

95
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:46,300
we first configure our new digital thermometer with the correct temperature

96
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,066
then we connect it to the molds

97
00:03:48,066 --> 00:03:50,200
and enable out output on redstone

98
00:03:50,466 --> 00:03:53,733
next we configure a pair of hoppers with the correct input ratio

99
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,733
and to avoid overfilling our crucible

100
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:58,133
we use a properly configured weight sensor

101
00:03:58,633 --> 00:04:00,866
and this simple system can easily be expanded

102
00:04:00,866 --> 00:04:02,600
to allow for more complex alloys

103
00:04:02,666 --> 00:04:04,000
such as stainless steel

104
00:04:04,466 --> 00:04:06,100
while this has many usages

105
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:08,333
we are also going to need some normal steel

106
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:10,633
which is made by pumping air in a crucible

107
00:04:10,666 --> 00:04:11,200
to do so

108
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,933
we will have to input kinetic energy to the crucible

109
00:04:13,933 --> 00:04:16,866
we can do that by vibrating it using a steam engine

110
00:04:17,433 --> 00:04:19,600
running this machine will require some steam

111
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:22,600
which it can produce by boiling water inside some boilers

112
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:26,800
which we heat up using the same burning boxes we use to heat up crucible

113
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,033
and now that we manage to obtain steels

114
00:04:29,033 --> 00:04:30,066
we can do many things

115
00:04:30,066 --> 00:04:32,000
starting from a bigger crucible

116
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:36,700
this one will be able to fit multiple blocks of metal easing the melting process

117
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:40,666
and the reason why we have minerals in the form of cubic meter size dust

118
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:42,600
is our new ore processing plant

119
00:04:42,666 --> 00:04:45,666
the first step is to run our rovers in a crusher

120
00:04:45,666 --> 00:04:48,300
which will break the big rocks into smaller chunks

121
00:04:48,433 --> 00:04:50,233
then we run those crushed rocks in a sluice

122
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:52,900
to separate the stone from the actual minerals

123
00:04:53,266 --> 00:04:55,733
next we run the purified ores through a centrifuge

124
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:57,233
to filter out more byproducts

125
00:04:57,300 --> 00:05:00,200
finally, we macerate all of the centrifuged ores in a shredder

126
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,900
to get everything in dust form

127
00:05:02,533 --> 00:05:05,900
however those dusts won't have all the same size

128
00:05:06,433 --> 00:05:08,266
to properly sort out all of those dust

129
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:09,900
we use a system of hoppers and funnels

130
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:12,633
to first cluster all of the dust into small size

131
00:05:12,633 --> 00:05:14,233
and then into full blocks

132
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:17,600
while most of those can be melted into pure metal using a crucible

133
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:19,800
others require some extra refinement

134
00:05:19,933 --> 00:05:22,533
so we built some ore-specific processing lines

135
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:24,200
like this one for aluminum

136
00:05:24,466 --> 00:05:26,233
to obtain this MV material

137
00:05:26,233 --> 00:05:27,866
we had to use an electrolyzer

138
00:05:27,866 --> 00:05:31,666
and you may be wondering why we aren't using electricity for other setups

139
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:33,800
well there are two main reasons

140
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:37,133
the first one is the horrible efficiency of transforming energy

141
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:40,933
and here I really want to be pedantic on what I mean with energy loss

142
00:05:40,933 --> 00:05:43,700
we start with a 25 percent loss when burning materials

143
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:46,200
to produce the heat units required to boil water

144
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:49,233
then a boiler will convert that heat into steam

145
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:50,866
if we use distilled water

146
00:05:50,866 --> 00:05:53,233
this process will be perfectly efficient

147
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,000
we pipe the steam to a turbine

148
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,100
which will dissipate one third of the energy

149
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:59,266
while using the hot gas to spin a rotor

150
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:01,333
these will produce a rotation unit

151
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:03,100
which we shaft to a dynamo

152
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:06,966
here after losing almost one more third of our energy to friction

153
00:06:06,966 --> 00:06:08,600
we finally get electricity

154
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:10,500
then we have the usual cable loss

155
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,100
which here is negligible

156
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,833
and after losing more than half of the starting energy

157
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:17,633
we figure out that most machines don't use electricity

158
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:21,233
so we have to deal with losing another half of our electric energy

159
00:06:21,266 --> 00:06:24,066
to convert it back to whatever we actually needed

160
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,700
the second issue is that

161
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:28,866
right now we can only shut off machines by cutting the power feed

162
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:35,000
so if we want to have the comfort of electricity versatility for machines that don't require too much power

163
00:06:35,033 --> 00:06:36,866
we will want some machines switch covers

164
00:06:36,866 --> 00:06:38,600
and also some battery boxes

165
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:41,733
however both of those things will require some circuit

166
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:45,500
and even the lowest tier of circuit requires plastic and silicone bottles

167
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:49,266
while the main issue of silicon is a bit of inert gas and processing time

168
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:52,933
making plastic has a mandatory titanium tetrachloride requirement

169
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:54,900
since we needed just a few drops

170
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:56,833
we manually handle all sorts of chemicals 

171
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:59,700
to process the bauxite leftovers into titanium

172
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:02,133
chemical reactors aren't a thing here

173
00:07:02,133 --> 00:07:05,100
so we had to deal with all sorts of never seen before machines

174
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:08,733
and after carefully measuring the correct amount of ingredients

175
00:07:08,733 --> 00:07:10,466
we made our first plastic

176
00:07:10,733 --> 00:07:13,000
with that we had every required ingredient

177
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:17,233
so we proceeded into quickly working everything into our first electric circuit

178
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:19,600
we use those to craft some machines which covers

179
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:22,433
and then we proceeded into building our LV workshop

180
00:07:22,433 --> 00:07:25,200
and since the some machines don't have an integrated motor

181
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:29,166
we still have to use a some bronze machine powered by dedicated electric motor

182
00:07:29,166 --> 00:07:31,600
we have already seen how inefficient that is

183
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:35,133
but being able to instantly start and stop those engines from the batteries

184
00:07:35,133 --> 00:07:37,800
is a really nice quality of life improvement

185
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:42,000
also there are some new forms of energy we can derive from electricity

186
00:07:42,033 --> 00:07:46,500
such as magnetic units made from an electromagnet to power polarizers

187
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:49,800
and laser units, made by a CO2 laser

188
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,733
which will have many usages in the future

189
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:54,600
but for now we can use that for a laser engraver

190
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:57,866
so that we can make LuV circuits, the highest tier available

191
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:00,400
with those we unlocked all sorts of cool things

192
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:02,933
and our first objective is going to be a nuclear reactor

193
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:04,733
to fix our energy production

194
00:08:04,866 --> 00:08:07,266
to get started, we are going to fuel it using uranium 238

195
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,033
which is super cheap

196
00:08:09,033 --> 00:08:12,066
and will keep producing heat for 800 hours

197
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,133
in this setup

198
00:08:13,133 --> 00:08:16,566
we are using some IC2 coolant to get the heat out of the reactor

199
00:08:16,566 --> 00:08:18,600
and bring it to some heat exchangers

200
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:21,666
where, as usual, we boil water to spin a turbine

201
00:08:21,733 --> 00:08:22,433
and this time

202
00:08:22,433 --> 00:08:25,333
to avoid using expensive cables that will also lose power

203
00:08:25,333 --> 00:08:27,266
we made a long shaft to our base

204
00:08:27,266 --> 00:08:31,100
where we have a small dynamo that slowly charges up some huge batteries

205
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:34,200
allowing the size for a bigger setup we will eventually build

206
00:08:34,533 --> 00:08:37,400
the first thing we will be using our new power source for

207
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,833
is a thermoelectric cooler

208
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:40,933
to run our new cryogenic distillation tower

209
00:08:40,933 --> 00:08:43,900
to obtain some noble gasses for a nano-scale fabricator

210
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,433
used to make graphene parts

211
00:08:45,433 --> 00:08:48,200
which have incredible stats despite being super cheap

212
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,633
notably, we can now make carbon crucibles

213
00:08:50,633 --> 00:08:53,333
capable of handling even the toughest materials

214
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:55,800
we are going to heat it up with our new electric heater

215
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:57,900
which perfectly manages temperature

216
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,833
and what we just made is tungsten carbide

217
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:04,500
used to make the better extruder capable of doing all sorts of jobs

218
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:08,200
however all of those new machines quickly drained our battery buffer

219
00:09:08,266 --> 00:09:10,700
it was clear we needed a bigger nuclear reactor

220
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,333
and to speed up the crafting process

221
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:17,333
we increased our efficiency by directly connecting our heaviest machinery to our old nuclear reactor

222
00:09:17,466 --> 00:09:19,400
and after crafting a lot of dense plates

223
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,900
we finally completed our new reactor plant

224
00:09:22,066 --> 00:09:24,200
this time we are using six reactor cores

225
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,066
filled with a mix of different rods

226
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:29,500
achieving a production of over 9000 heat units per thick

227
00:09:29,866 --> 00:09:32,633
we use some of that heater to keep the water loop going

228
00:09:32,633 --> 00:09:35,600
and the rest goes into heating two large invar boilers

229
00:09:35,733 --> 00:09:38,700
those will produce a 16,000 liters of steam per tick

230
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:40,733
which we use to spin a large turbine

231
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:43,600
with an output of 5,000 rotation units per tick

232
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:47,200
finally, a large dynamo will convert that into 4000 EU per tick

233
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:48,866
just below the IV result

234
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:51,000
the reason why the output isn't consistent

235
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,633
is that we aren't using that energy

236
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:55,233
and the batteries in our buffer are fully charged

237
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:00,833
大家好

238
00:00:00,833 --> 00:00:03,233
今天我们要在格雷科技 6 中展开新的冒险

239
00:00:03,233 --> 00:00:04,466
当我们环顾四周时

240
00:00:04,466 --> 00:00:06,033
会发现一些地表岩石

241
00:00:06,033 --> 00:00:08,600
我们可以把它们收集起来，做出第一把斧头

242
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:11,133
它甚至不需要工作台就能制作

243
00:00:11,233 --> 00:00:12,266
这把斧头很便宜

244
00:00:12,266 --> 00:00:14,700
而且能一次砍倒多根原木

245
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:16,833
不过它很慢，耐久也很低

246
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:19,600
因为它是用大理石石子做成的

247
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,666
如果我们再多看一看

248
00:00:21,666 --> 00:00:23,666
就会发现还真有更好的石子

249
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:25,800
花了时间收集石头之后

250
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:28,400
我们发现红花岗岩是最好的

251
00:00:28,866 --> 00:00:31,800
用这种石头做的工具甚至能挖黑曜石

252
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:33,266
不过速度就没那么快了

253
00:00:33,266 --> 00:00:35,300
这些工具毕竟还是石子做的

254
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:37,066
耐久还是很低

255
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:38,433
但这也没什么大不了

256
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:40,033
因为我们只要再去找找石子

257
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:41,600
就能找到更多这种材料

258
00:00:42,066 --> 00:00:43,466
一旦我们找到整块的原石

259
00:00:43,466 --> 00:00:45,700
只要用锤子把石头敲两次

260
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:48,133
就能拿到需要的所有石子

261
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:51,133
要做更好的工具，我们还要加工一些金属

262
00:00:51,133 --> 00:00:53,233
但首先我们要找个合适的居所

263
00:00:53,233 --> 00:00:55,300
在那里开始建设我们的工业基地

264
00:00:55,666 --> 00:00:57,533
毕竟以后我们可能还需要氯气

265
00:00:57,533 --> 00:00:59,733
所以住在海岸附近应该不错

266
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,600
这当然不是借口

267
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:04,533
只是为了让我们能有一座美观，能看到落日的海景房

268
00:01:04,533 --> 00:01:06,333
忙完这一切之后

269
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:07,833
我们终于可以稍微休息一下

270
00:01:07,833 --> 00:01:10,633
一边炫点路上找到的甜浆果

271
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:15,000
这时候我们发现，吃太多甜食并不健康

272
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:19,200
第二天，我们决定开始建一个像样的菜园，来调整饮食

273
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:20,666
但在挖开一些石头之后

274
00:01:20,666 --> 00:01:23,933
我们发现土壤里有很高的铜含量

275
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,233
于是我们开始往下挖，进一步调查

276
00:01:26,233 --> 00:01:29,066
结果挖出了越来越多富铜的岩石

277
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:32,533
不过铜本身并不是很好的工具材料

278
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:33,466
要让它更硬一些

279
00:01:33,466 --> 00:01:36,666
还得加入一些在后院找到的锡

280
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:39,266
但要把这两种金属真正合金在一起

281
00:01:39,266 --> 00:01:42,466
得把混合物加热到 1400 K

282
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:44,833
这一步必须在坩埚里完成

283
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:46,900
坩埚可以很容易用黏土做出来

284
00:01:47,133 --> 00:01:47,900
要把坩埚加热

285
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:50,500
我们在它下面点燃燃烧室

286
00:01:50,833 --> 00:01:53,100
现在只要把原料扔进去

287
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:54,800
等它们全部融化就行

288
00:01:55,066 --> 00:01:56,733
一旦混合物变成正确的颜色

289
00:01:56,733 --> 00:01:59,666
我们就能把熔融金属倒进镐头模具里

290
00:02:00,266 --> 00:02:02,066
为了庆祝青铜时代的到来

291
00:02:02,066 --> 00:02:03,333
我们可以做一个巨型三明治

292
00:02:03,333 --> 00:02:05,400
然后一口吃下去

293
00:02:05,900 --> 00:02:08,933
吃完了，坩埚也变黄了

294
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:11,433
话还没说完

295
00:02:11,433 --> 00:02:12,666
坩埚就熔化了

296
00:02:13,033 --> 00:02:16,333
没错，在 GT6 里，万物都有熔点

297
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:18,200
要多快达到熔点

298
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:20,233
取决于我们要加热物品的热容

299
00:02:20,233 --> 00:02:23,033
以及我们对它输入了多少热量

300
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:27,100
虽然我们也能通过坩埚的颜色来大致判断温度

301
00:02:27,100 --> 00:02:29,066
但更好的办法是做一个温度计

302
00:02:29,466 --> 00:02:31,600
要做温度计，我们需要一些水银

303
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:33,866
于是我们启程去寻找新的矿物

304
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,266
在探索过程中

305
00:02:35,266 --> 00:02:37,000
我们发现了大量煤矿

306
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,200
还有大量富铁砂

307
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:41,900
我们在地下还发现了各种各样的矿

308
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,433
其中有些还挺难一眼看见

309
00:02:44,733 --> 00:02:46,833
我们还找到了一座奇怪的建筑

310
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:49,866
进去之后才发现，那是一个废弃基地

311
00:02:49,866 --> 00:02:51,833
里面堆满了各种化学品

312
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:54,400
还有大量各种金属

313
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:57,800
我们还在附近的抽屉里找到了已经加工好的金属零件

314
00:02:57,900 --> 00:03:00,300
如果这些都还不够多的话

315
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:03,666
我们又找到了青铜时代的圣杯：一个打火机

316
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:06,133
这东西的点火成功率可是 100%

317
00:03:06,133 --> 00:03:08,333
我们甚至还找到了备用丙烷来给它补充燃料

318
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,600
虽然我们在这里发现了水银

319
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:13,633
但我们还是继续探索更多区域，以确保有稳定来源

320
00:03:14,033 --> 00:03:15,466
我们穿越了多个维度

321
00:03:15,466 --> 00:03:17,633
直到最终找到一条红石矿脉

322
00:03:17,633 --> 00:03:20,533
其中含有朱砂，一种富汞矿物

323
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:24,066
我们加工原矿以提高产量

324
00:03:24,066 --> 00:03:25,400
最后我们把它加热

325
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,833
提取一些水银做温度计

326
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:32,033
有了这个，我们终于能更精确地测量温度了

327
00:03:32,033 --> 00:03:34,066
也让合金制作更容易控制

328
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:39,066
下一步是把温度计接到红石传感器上

329
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:41,700
这样我们就能自动化合金

330
00:03:42,066 --> 00:03:42,700
要做到这一点

331
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:46,300
我们先把新的数字温度计按正确温度配置好

332
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,066
然后把它连接到模具上

333
00:03:48,066 --> 00:03:50,200
并在打开“有红石时自动输出”

334
00:03:50,466 --> 00:03:53,733
接着我们设置一对漏斗，调整到正确的输入比例

335
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,733
要避免坩埚被灌满

336
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:58,133
我们可以用一个调好配置的重量传感器

337
00:03:58,633 --> 00:04:00,866
这个简单系统很容易扩展

338
00:04:00,866 --> 00:04:02,600
来支持更复杂的合金

339
00:04:02,666 --> 00:04:04,000
比如不锈钢

340
00:04:04,466 --> 00:04:06,100
虽然不锈钢用途很广

341
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:08,333
我们还是需要一些普通钢材

342
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:10,633
普通钢是通过向坩埚里泵入空气制成的

343
00:04:10,666 --> 00:04:11,200
要输入空气

344
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,933
我们得给坩埚输入动能

345
00:04:13,933 --> 00:04:16,866
我们可以靠蒸汽机来振动坩埚

346
00:04:17,433 --> 00:04:19,600
运行这台机器需要一些蒸汽

347
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:22,600
而蒸汽可以通过锅炉烧水来产生

348
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:26,800
加热锅炉用的是和加热坩埚时相同的燃烧室

349
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,033
我们既然已经成功做出了钢

350
00:04:29,033 --> 00:04:30,066
那就可以做很多事情了

351
00:04:30,066 --> 00:04:32,000
先从更大的坩埚开始

352
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:36,700
这种坩埚可以容纳下一些金属块，简化熔化过程

353
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:40,666
而矿石之所以会以立方米大小的粉尘形式出现

354
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:42,600
是因为我们有了新的矿石处理厂

355
00:04:42,666 --> 00:04:45,666
第一步是把原矿送进研磨机

356
00:04:45,666 --> 00:04:48,300
把大块岩石打成更小的碎块

357
00:04:48,433 --> 00:04:50,233
然后把这些碎石送进洗矿槽

358
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:52,900
把石头和真正的矿物分开

359
00:04:53,266 --> 00:04:55,733
接着把净化后的矿石送入离心机

360
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:57,233
分离出更多副产物

361
00:04:57,300 --> 00:05:00,200
最后把所有离心后的矿石送进粉碎机

362
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,900
把它们全部打成粉尘

363
00:05:02,533 --> 00:05:05,900
不过这些粉尘的粒度并不统一

364
00:05:06,433 --> 00:05:08,266
要把这些粉尘正确分拣好

365
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:09,900
我们用的是漏斗和料斗系统

366
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:12,633
先把所有粉尘聚成小撮粉

367
00:05:12,633 --> 00:05:14,233
再聚成整块

368
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:17,600
虽然其中大多数都能在坩埚里熔成纯金属

369
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:19,800
但有些还需要额外精炼

370
00:05:19,933 --> 00:05:22,533
所以我们又建立了一些矿专用的生产线

371
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:24,200
比如这条铝生产线

372
00:05:24,466 --> 00:05:26,233
要得到这种 MV 级材料

373
00:05:26,233 --> 00:05:27,866
我们不得不用电解机

374
00:05:27,866 --> 00:05:31,666
你可能想问，为什么其他设备不用电力驱动

375
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:33,800
原因主要有两个

376
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:37,133
第一个就是能量转换效率低得离谱

377
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:40,933
这里我要特别较真地解释一下我说的能量损耗

378
00:05:40,933 --> 00:05:43,700
我们先从燃料燃烧时损失 25% 开始算

379
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:46,200
把燃料转成烧开水所需的热能

380
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:49,233
然后锅炉再把热量转成蒸汽

381
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:50,866
如果用的是蒸馏水

382
00:05:50,866 --> 00:05:53,233
这个过程就是完全高效的

383
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,000
我们把蒸汽送进涡轮机

384
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,100
在那里又会损失三分之一的能量

385
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:59,266
同时用高温气体去带动转子

386
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:01,333
这样就会产生转动能

387
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:03,100
再把它传给发电机

388
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:06,966
这里又因为摩擦损失了将近三分之一的能量

389
00:06:06,966 --> 00:06:08,600
最后我们才真正发出电来

390
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:10,500
然后还有常见的电缆损耗

391
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,100
不过在这里几乎可以忽略不计

392
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,833
等我们损失掉超过一半的初始能量后

393
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:17,633
就会发现大多数机器根本不用电

394
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:21,200
所以我们还得再把剩下那一半电能转回去

395
00:06:21,266 --> 00:06:24,066
变成我们真正需要的能量形式

396
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,700
第二个问题是

397
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:28,866
现在我们只能通过切断供电来关闭机器

398
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:35,000
所以如果我们想让那些耗电不多的机器也能方便地使用电力

399
00:06:35,033 --> 00:06:36,866
就需要一些机器开关覆盖板

400
00:06:36,866 --> 00:06:38,600
再加上一些电池箱

401
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:41,733
不过这两样东西都需要电路板

402
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:45,500
但最低级的电路板也要塑料和硅胶瓶

403
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:49,266
硅的主要问题在于需要惰性气体和处理时间长

404
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:52,933
而制作塑料则必须用到四氯化钛

405
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:54,900
因为我们只需要几滴

406
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:56,833
所以我们直接手搓这些化学品

407
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:59,700
用来铝土矿废料处理成钛

408
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:02,133
GT6 并没有化学反应釜这种东西

409
00:07:02,133 --> 00:07:05,100
所以我们只好面对各种前所未见的机器

410
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:08,733
仔细量好正确配比之后

411
00:07:08,733 --> 00:07:10,466
我们做出了第一批塑料

412
00:07:10,733 --> 00:07:13,000
这下所需材料就全齐了

413
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:17,233
于是我们很快把所有材料搓成了第一个电路板

414
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:19,600
我们用第一批电路板来制作机器开关覆盖板

415
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:22,433
然后开始建造我们的 LV 车间

416
00:07:22,433 --> 00:07:25,200
而且因为有些机器没有内置电机

417
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:29,166
我们还是得用一些由专用电机驱动的青铜机器

418
00:07:29,166 --> 00:07:31,600
我们已经见过这有多低效

419
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:35,133
但能用电池瞬间启停这些引擎

420
00:07:35,133 --> 00:07:37,800
确实是个很不错的体验提升

421
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:42,000
另外，我们还能从电力中得到出一些新的能量形式

422
00:07:42,033 --> 00:07:46,500
比如用电磁铁制成的磁能，用来驱动极化器

423
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:49,800
以及由二氧化碳激光器制成的激光能

424
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,733
它们未来会有很多用途

425
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:54,600
现在，我们可以先用它来做激光刻蚀机

426
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:57,866
这样就能制作 LuV 电路板，目前最高等级的电路板

427
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:00,400
有了这些，我们就解锁了各种很酷的东西

428
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:02,933
我们的第一个目标是建造一座核反应堆

429
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:04,733
来填上我们的能源生产

430
00:08:04,866 --> 00:08:07,333
首先，我们打算用铀 238 作为燃料

431
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,033
这种燃料超级便宜

432
00:08:09,033 --> 00:08:12,066
而且能持续产热 800 小时

433
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,133
在这个方案里

434
00:08:13,133 --> 00:08:16,566
我们用的是 IC2 冷却剂，把反应堆里的热量导出去

435
00:08:16,566 --> 00:08:18,600
再把它送到热交换器里

436
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:21,666
接下来照例是烧水来推动涡轮机

437
00:08:21,733 --> 00:08:22,433
这一次

438
00:08:22,433 --> 00:08:25,333
为了避免使用同样昂贵、还会损耗电力的电缆

439
00:08:25,333 --> 00:08:27,266
我们拉了一根长长的传动轴回基地

440
00:08:27,266 --> 00:08:31,100
基地里有一台小发电机，慢慢给大电池组充电

441
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:34,200
这样以后我们还能继续扩建更大的系统

442
00:08:34,533 --> 00:08:37,400
我们这个新电源要先供给的第一件设备是

443
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,833
半导体制冷器

444
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:40,933
用来运行新的低温蒸馏塔

445
00:08:40,933 --> 00:08:43,900
从而获取一些惰性气体，做纳米级制造机

446
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,433
从而生产石墨烯部件

447
00:08:45,433 --> 00:08:48,200
这些部件性能惊人，却依然便宜得离谱

448
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,633
值得一提的是，我们现在还能制作碳坩埚

449
00:08:50,633 --> 00:08:53,333
它们足以应付最难处理的材料

450
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:55,800
我们会用新的电加热器来加热它

451
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:57,900
它能把温度控制得非常精确

452
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,833
我们刚做出来的是碳化钨

453
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:04,500
它用于制造更好的压模机，能完成各种工作

454
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:08,200
不过这些新机器很快就耗尽了我们存的电

455
00:09:08,266 --> 00:09:10,700
很明显，我们需要更大的反应堆

456
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,333
同时也要加快制作速度

457
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:17,333
于是我们把耗能最高的机器直接连到旧反应堆上，以提高效率

458
00:09:17,466 --> 00:09:19,400
在制作了大量致密板之后

459
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,900
我们终于完成了新的反应堆

460
00:09:22,066 --> 00:09:24,200
这一次我们用了六个反应堆堆芯

461
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,066
填入了不同燃料棒的组合

462
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:29,500
实现了超过 9000 HU/t 的产量

463
00:09:29,866 --> 00:09:32,633
其中一部分热量用来维持水循环

464
00:09:32,633 --> 00:09:35,600
剩下的则用来加热两台大型殷钢锅炉

465
00:09:35,733 --> 00:09:38,700
它们可以产出 16,000 L/t 蒸汽

466
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:40,733
这些蒸汽用来带动一台大型涡轮机

467
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:43,600
输出达到 5,000 RU/t

468
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:47,200
最后，用大型发电机把它变成 4,000 EU/t

469
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:48,866
刚好低于 IV 电压

470
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:51,000
输出之所以不稳定

471
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,633
是因为我们没有在消耗这些能量

472
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:55,233
而电池箱里的电池已经充满了

